This mobile phone data plan seems valuable based on your location . However , you should note that this data plan is not like your phone ' s internal antenna and has significantly better coverage . My phone has four networks available , but in my area , there are two or three unstable networks that constantly go up and down . This data plan locks onto three networks and keeps them stable . Another thing I noticed is that this data plan needs to be connected to an adapter with at least 1 Amp . I tried it with the original adapter ( Huawei 550mAh ) and saw that in the 4G coverage , it would intermittently turn on and off . But when I connected it to a 1 Amp adapter , the download speed increased and remained relatively stable . Of course , you can also connect it to a 2 Amp adapter . It ' s also worth noting that this data plan is programmed to automatically turn off after 10 minutes of inactivity and automatically turns on when you start using the internet . You can change this setting from 5 to 30 or 120 minutes . Regarding the external antenna , it ' s worth mentioning that this data plan doesn ' t have an external antenna . But you can connect an external antenna ts5 . The software is also very easy , both the mobile network link and the Hilink app . You can easily connect other data packages and activate them without any problems .
